headline: What Analysts Think Gives Delta Air Lines NYSE DAL A Changing Edge In The Story
summary: Delta Air Lines just saw its fair value estimate nudged from US$73.64 to US$74.61, a modest shift that lines up with recent research turning more positive on its Q3 performance and Q4 guidance. The slightly lower discount rate and a small adjustment to long term revenue growth assumptions mirror analysts’ view that Delta could be positioned to benefit from what they see as structural advantages and a supportive mix of premium and domestic demand, while still acknowledging execution risks...
